<item>
            <title>[SPARK-33472] IllegalArgumentException when applying RemoveRedundantSorts before EnsureRequirements</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-33472</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;`RemoveRedundantSorts` rule uses SparkPlan&apos;s `outputPartitioning` to check whether a sort node is redundant. Currently, it is added before `EnsureRequirements`. Since `PartitioningCollection` requires left and right partitioning to have the same number of partitions, which is not necessarily true before applying `EnsureRequirements`, the rule can fail with the following exception:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;IllegalArgumentException: requirement failed: PartitioningCollection requires all of its partitionings have the same numPartitions.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should switch the order between these two rules to satisfy the requirement when instantiating `PartitioningCollection`.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
